<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="A" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Adversity" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Adversity,</orth> misfortune, calamity: <bibl n="shak. tgv 4.1" default="NO" valid="yes">Gent. IV, 1, 12</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. err 2.1" default="NO" valid="yes">Err. II, 1, 34</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. err 4.4" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 4, 21</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ayl 2.1" default="NO" valid="yes">As II, 1, 12</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h6 4.4" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A IV, 4, 14</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 3h6 3.1.24" default="NO" valid="yes">H6C III, 1, 24</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. rom 3.3.55" default="NO" valid="yes">Rom. III, 3, 55</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. oth 1.3.274" default="NO" valid="yes">Oth. I, 3, 274</bibl> (<emph>--ies</emph>). Abstr. pro concr.: <cit><quote>well said, a.!</quote> <bibl n="shak. tro 5.1.14" default="NO" valid="yes">Troil. V, 1, 14</bibl></cit>, i. e. mischievous and offensive creature.
